../org-agent-skills/org/org-level-skill-generation.log:409:You may use subagents during iteration to validate whether a skill works on realistic tasks or whether a suspected problem is real. This is most useful when you want an independent pass on the skill's behavior, outputs, or failure modes after a revision.  Only do this when it is possible to start new subagents.
../org-agent-skills/org/org-level-skill-generation.log:417:Every skill consists of a required SKILL.md file and optional bundled resources:
../org-agent-skills/org/org-level-skill-generation.log:421:├── SKILL.md (required)
